# Post System

This is a simple RESTful API for managing posts using GoLang, Gorilla Mux, and GORM.

## Getting Started

These instructions will get you a copy of the project up and running on your local machine for development and testing purposes.

### Prerequisites

- GoLang
- Gin
- GORM
- PostgreSQL

### Installing

Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/your-username/post-system.git

Navigate to the project directory:
cd post-system

Install the required packages:
go mod tidy

### Configuration
Create a .env file in the root of the project and add your database credentials:
APP_HOST=localhost
APP_PORT=8000
APP_LOG_PATH=logs

DATABASE_HOST=localhost
DATABASE_PORT=5432
DATABASE_USER=admin
DATABASE_PASSWORD=
DATABASE_NAME=post_system

### Running the application
Build and run the application:
go build -o main
./main

The application will start listening on localhost:8080.

### API Endpoints
GET /api/posts: Get all posts
POST /api/posts: Create a new post
GET /api/posts/{id}: Get a post by ID
PUT /api/posts/{id}: Update a post by ID
DELETE /api/posts/{id}: Delete a post by ID

